# Routing and Handoffs

- Route work to one best next move before broad implementation.
- Keep plans bounded, practical, and sequence-aware.
- Prefer decomposition that reduces risk and preserves momentum.
- Handoffs must include:
  - goal and scope
  - files touched
  - validation status (verified/unverified)
  - risks
  - one next bounded follow-up

